《'''It's on Again'''》是一首由美国唱片艺人[[艾莉西亚·凯斯|艾莉西亚·凯斯]]与美国说唱艺人[[肯德里克·拉玛尔|肯德里克·拉玛尔]]合唱的歌曲。该歌曲为2014年电影《[[蜘蛛人：驚奇再起2|蜘蛛人：驚奇再起2]]》所写，写作者是凯斯和拉玛尔，电影配乐是[[汉斯·齐默|汉斯·齐默]]，制作人是[[法瑞尔·威廉斯|法瑞尔·威廉斯]]<ref name="Billboard">{{cite journal |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5930428/alicia-keys-kendrick-lamar-team-for-its-on-again-on-spider-man-2-soundtrack |title=Alicia Keys, Kendrick Lamar Team for 'It's On Again' on 'Spider-Man 2' Soundtrack |work=[[告示牌_(雜誌)|Billboard]] |location=New York |date=March 11, 2014 |accessdate=April 9, 2014 |author=Rutherford, Kevin |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112025918/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5930428/alicia-keys-kendrick-lamar-team-for-its-on-again-on-spider-man-2-soundtrack |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《It's on Again》是以《惊奇蜘蛛侠2》原声带首支单曲的形式于2014年3月31日发行的。

==发行==
2014年3月12日，[[哥伦比亚唱片|哥伦比亚唱片]]发布了新闻称：《It's on Again》将会被包括在《惊奇蜘蛛侠2》原声带中，且作为电影的片尾曲<ref name="PR">{{cite press release |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-amazing-spider-man-2-to-include-its-on-again-by-alicia-keys-featuring-kendrick-lamar-written-by-pharrell-williams-alicia-keys-hans-zimmer-and-kendrick-lamar-249701151.html |title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' To Include 'It's On Again' by Alicia Keys Featuring Kendrick Lamar Written by Pharrell Williams, Alicia Keys, Hans Zimmer, and Kendrick Lamar |publisher=[[Columbia_Records|Columbia Records]] |agency=[[PR_Newswire|PR Newswire]] |location=New York |date=March 12, 2014 |accessdate=April 9, 2014 |archive-date=2014-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408225053/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-amazing-spider-man-2-to-include-its-on-again-by-alicia-keys-featuring-kendrick-lamar-written-by-pharrell-williams-alicia-keys-hans-zimmer-and-kendrick-lamar-249701151.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。The release included a statement from director [[Marc_Webb|Marc Webb]], who described the process of selecting "a song that would be upbeat and exciting, but also contain a note of foreboding" to serve as the film's the closing theme and praised "It's on Again" as the "perfect end note."<ref name="PR"/> Keys also expressed her excitement at working with Kendrick Lamar, producer [[Pharrell_Williams|Pharrell Williams]] and film composer [[Hans_Zimmer|Hans Zimmer]], the latter of whom scores the film.<ref name="PR"/> On March 31, "It's on Again" was uploaded to Keys' official [[Soundcloud|Soundcloud]] page<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pitchfork.com/news/54320-kendrick-lamar-and-alicia-keys-share-pharrell-produced-the-amazing-spider-man-2-collaboration-its-on-again/ |title=Kendrick Lamar and Alicia Keys Share Pharrell-Produced The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Collaboration 'It's On Again' |publisher=[[Pitchfork_Media|Pitchfork Media]] |date=March 31, 2014 |accessdate=April 9, 2014 |author1=Minsker, Evan |author2=Gordon, Jeremy |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111215122/http://pitchfork.com/news/54320-kendrick-lamar-and-alicia-keys-share-pharrell-produced-the-amazing-spider-man-2-collaboration-its-on-again/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> and impacted [[urban_contemporary|mainstream urban]] radio in the United States.<ref name="MainstreamUrban"/> The following day, it was released [[music_download|digitally]] as a single.<ref name="iTunesUS"/>

==商业性演出==
"It's on Again" debuted on the ''[[告示牌_(雜誌)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard_charts#R&B/Hip-Hop|Adult R&B Songs]] and [[Hot_R&B/Hip-Hop_Airplay|Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay]] charts at numbers 17 and 40 respectively on the chart week ending April 19, 2014.<ref name="Debut">{{cite journal |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6041343/chart-highlights-coldplay-ties-u2-for-most-adult-alternative |title=Chart Highlights: Coldplay Ties U2 For Most Adult Alternative Songs No. 1s |work=Billboard |location=New York |date=April 7, 2014 |accessdate=April 9, 2014 |author=Trust, Gary |archive-date=2020-04-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200426013401/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6041343/chart-highlights-coldplay-ties-u2-for-most-adult-alternative |dead-url=no }}</ref>

